<para>
  Select &skel; &elems; that are <link
  linkend="Section-Concepts-Skeleton-Homogeneity">heterogeneous</link>.
  Any &elem; whose homogeneity is less than the given
  <varname>threshold</varname> will be selected.
</para>
<figure id="Figure-HeteroElements">
  <title>Selecting Heterogeneous Elements</title>
  <mediaobject>
    <imageobject>
	  <imagedata fileref="FIGURES/skel_selection/select_elhomog.png"
                 contentwidth="630px" format="PNG"/>
    </imageobject>
    <caption>
	  <simpara>
	    (a) A &skel; containing some heterogeneous &elems;.  The
	    pixels have been grouped by <link
	    linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Image.AutoGroup">color</link>, so
	    &elems; straddling two or more colors are inhomogeneous.
      </simpara>
      <simpara>
        (b) The &elems; (in red) that are less than 80% homogeneous
        have been selected.
	  </simpara>
    </caption>
  </mediaobject>
</figure>

